there were some way to turn the ooc channel off.  If only Verant would set it up so you could click options, channels, and turn OOC channel off until the newness of the server dies down some and people shut up.<br><br>The Horror!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! <br><br>What's this now?  People aren't running up to you and regailing you with stories about how they were kidnapped by a band of gnomish gypsies, abandoned in Kithicor forest, and raised by a dread wolf as one of her cubs?  Oh god, please tell me it isn't so.  You might have to actually approach other players and INITIATE a conversation with them.  AAAAAHHH!!  NOOOOOO!!!!!<br><br>God, can you all whine a little more?  Sheesh.  <br><br>I started off in Qeynos, city of men.  Of all the cities in the world, it's probably the least hospitable from a roleplaying standpoint (players there don't share a common background, it attracts a lot of new players who can't find their way to the bank / figure out how to use channels / etc).  Here's what I saw...<br><br>Groups of people milling around by the rip-off merchants kinda near the bank just chatting with eachother about their character's histories n such.<br><br>Some guy fishing who'd worked in some emotes to use when he cast his line.<br><br>A ton of half-elves speaking in elven, referring to eachother as brother &amp; sister.<br><br>More people referring to their diety when they cast a spell than I could count (ie: May Karana watch over you, etc)<br><br>A few erudite caster groups who sailed over, refusing to speak in human because it was beneath them.<br><br>A lot of players grouping, tearing up the gnoll population, and just having fun.<br><br>Sure, there were a few kill stealers, and a few people who had no intention of ever roleplaying, but God, how freaking old are you if you can't ignore that?<br><br>I have TWO people on my ignore list right now, and NEITHER one of them are Kewl-d00ds.  Ya know who they are?  Spazzed out roleplayers who can't shut the hell up.  They sit there screaming on the zone-wide channels &quot;So-and-so shouts: STOP USING THIS FOR OOC!  This is the roleplay server!  If you don't want to roleplay, WHY ARE YOU HERE?!?!&quot;  etc.  <br><br>My apologies, but that ruins my roleplaying experience a hell of a lot more than some guy who goes /shout Ding!<br><br>So, I guess it's MY turn to be bitchy.  If you can't handle the fact that people are as people do, and won't ALWAYS be roleplaying, why don't you march your lazy ass on down to Target and pick up a copy of Dark Ages of Camelot so the GMs can babysit the server for you.<br><br>Thanx.<br><br>- Syllestrae Silverblade<br>Drunken Bard of Rallos Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uanklesdirtyfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ankles Dirtyfoot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/9/01 4:53:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Quit yer bitchin!</span><hr size=1> Well said!<br><br>My theory has always been: if you don't want to hear it, don't listen.<br><br>I've found that a lot of the roleplayers are shy, and unsure of who is open to RP and who isn't. All it usually takes is one comment or emote to get the ball rolling.<br><br>This afternoon I was sprinkled with drops of holy water from Prexus by an Erudite getting off the boat in Qeynos.<br><br>Ran into an atheist Wizard with loud political leanings..<br><br>Stopped to talk to a solo Erudite in Toxxulia, who was mourning the death of her sister and swearing revenge on the Kobold clan..<br><br>Also happened to meet someone named &quot;Lozerkid&quot; who inspected me 4 times and challenged me to duel twice that number, after I politely declined each time since I was waiting to board the ship.<br><br>But all in all, the good experiences far outweigh the bad. You just have to open up to people, and go out on a limb sometimes. <p><table width="400" height="125" border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0"><tr><td valign="top" align="left" width="95" height="125"><img src="http://losingheidi.freeservers.com/face.gif"></td><td  valign="top" align="left" width="305"><font face="arial, system, courier new" size="-1" color="black"><b>Ankles Dirtyfoot</b><br><i>Black-soled, bow-slinging hippie of Karana</i><br>Firiona Vie - DN</font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufleshweapon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fleshweapon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/9/01 5:23:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_tongue.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Quit yer bitchin!</span><hr size=1> Yup,i have to agree...just turn off /ooc<br>I really wish i could have encountered those erud sailors,sounds like they're having a blast. <p>Klug Da Spiritfist<Br>Wulfbrudder ob Oggok<Br>Fironia Vie<Br>Yoo gunna eat dat,ur whut?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image