&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Quit yer bitchin!</span><hr size=1> Ember-I'm horribly sorry that you let others control whether or not you have a good time. <br><br>Evangelina-/cheer *Smile*  <br><br>And I&quot;m loving all these stories of great times, they make me smile, and make me wanna log back in*chuckle* <p><center><a href="http://sarshouse.homestead.com/files/index.htm"><img src="http://sarshouse.homestead.com/files/images/sarhea.gif"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujantisconstanceeorle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jantis ConstanceEorle</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/9/01 11:08:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.warghoul.com/images/CoSS/jantis_head_ez.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Quit yer bitchin!</span><hr size=1> I agree that there should be an /ooc channel.  There is absolutely nothing wrong with out of character in a roleplaying environment.  Even sitting around a pen and paper rpg, you occasionally have to say &quot;Hold on a second, phone&quot; or &quot;Gotta take a wiz, anyone need anything while I'm up?&quot;<br><br>I think the dumbest element in this server is the removal of the /ooc channel.  I loved being able to turn it off.  What I hated was the lack of respect for people that wanted to use /auction for more than /auction and /shout for anything other than in-character shouting.  I turn of /ooc for a reason.  It is there for a reason.<br><br>To remove it from this server is COMPLETELY counter-procuctive.  That being said...<br><br>There is no /ooc.  That doesn't mean /shout or /auction is your new /ooc channel.  If you don't like it, then complain to Verant.  If you want a petition to put /ooc back in, I'd love to sign it, for reasons stated above.  But for now, there is no /ooc channel, so don't complain to other people that are using the channel for appropriate use to get angry at you for going around the rules, which is what you are doing when you don't use the proper channel.<br><br>It's no different than getting caught speeding.  If you drive over the limit, don't blame the policeman that caught you or the person that lives in the neighborhood for reporting you.  Go to the city council and argue that the speed limit needs to be raised... but it was you that decided to break the rules and it's you that needs to suck it up if you get caught.<br><br>Of course, it's a 90% moot point, since most of the time the policeman just shrugs and lets you off with a warning... if they even bother stopping you.<br><br>p.s. I agree 100% that the people that bitch about it in the same channel are just as guilty.  It annoys the hell out of me as well, and I cheer your complaints of them.  I don't agree that they should have to suck it up, but they certainly gain nothing by spamming the channel even more. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uliusadh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Liusadh</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.elchtom.de/Fantasy/f75.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usert