izza example elsewhere.  The point is that without an /ooc channel, nobody is supposed to have any means whatsoever to discuss things that are out of character.  That includes game mechanics.  That includes assistance with problems that you can't put into roleplaying terms without sounding stupid.  <br><br>I personally would have no reason to use /ooc to tell people that I'm going to the bathroom, considering the whole zone could care less.  The only time I can imagine using /ooc for that would be a full zone raid, like Hate or Fear.  Even there, you can tell your group and put the /afk tag on.<br><br>That being said, yes there are a lot of jerks that are going overboard with their idea of roleplaying.  So are there dewds and griefers breaking the channel usage of /auction and /shout.  Verant took out /ooc for this server not for others to spam the other channels with ooc discussions.  If you have a problem with that, then talk to Verant about it.  Maybe they will listen to us and reinstate /ooc so I can turn it off and the problem is solved.<br><br>I've said it before, if someone is spamming a channel for a use other than its purpose (shout = in character zonewide communication, auction = in-character merchant-type activities) then /petition them.  This includes /ooc conversation of any kind, which includes people bitching about people not roleplaying.<br><br>To me, spamming the /ooc channel with &quot;THIS IS ROLEPLAYING, STOP USING THIS CHANNEL!!!&quot; is no different than a librarian constantly shouting for people to be quiet in a library.<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>As for zealots... there are different degrees of people who roleplay.  I have met many wonderful people that do live action roleplaying as well as are involved with such groups as the SCA.  I used to, but kept moving around and got tired of keeping track of things.  Just because someone enjoys something that you don't understand doesn't mean they are zealots.  My only problem is when people don't know what to stop.  There is a time to roleplay and a time to be in real life.<br><br>Would I have a problem with you saying you have to go afk?   No.  AFK is an ooc term... my character would never tell someone they were going away from keyboard then stare into the distance for five minutes.  Personally, I enjoy a relaxed environment and would adapt to the people I am with.  If people want to stay in character in group, then great!  If not, that's cool with me too.  Very specifically, this is a roleplay preferred server, not a roleplay enforced server, so you don't have to be in character at all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukorraisashadowsgate.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korraisa Shadowsgate</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Bonecollecter</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/17/01 8:22:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=19>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Quit yer bitchin!</span><hr size=1> OoC: Personally I just ignore or seethe behind the screen.  I try to set am example for the others in the zone; and no it's not because I am snob and want others to look up to me...it seems to me that perhaps if enough people do something that it may sink in one of those Other people conscieness(sp?) and they will someday go...&quot;oh, so that's how you do it.&quot;  It may takes mont